The paper deals with hyperparameter optimization of deep neural networks, which is a common problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) since deep neural networks are commonly used in these fields. The paper also mentions the use of Bayesian optimization, which is a popular technique in optimization and search algorithms, suggesting that it could also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with the performance of deep neural networks, which could also fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
